commit.message: added precision parameter to to_s() and pretty(), fixes #21

Support unit without B suffix

e.g. Kubernetes uses this format: https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/assign-memory-resource/#memory-units

Accept unicode space characters

[[:space:]] includes unicode space characters too, so when Nokogiri interprets "12.3 MiB" as "12.3\u00A0MiB", Filesize will still work.

[[:blank:]] might be even better because it doesn't include newline and carriage returns.

Include offending string in error message (#14)

As an aid to debugging, including the string that filesize was unable to parse in the error message.

Add compatibility for Ruby 1.8

Generally, we wouldn't support such an old Ruby version. In this case,
however, only a tiny amount of changes was required, and people actually
asked for compatibility.
Use proper glob for files in gemspec
Don't set a date in gemspec

Remove changelog

We never maintained it, anyway.

fix display of binary units

Kibibytes were displayed as `kiB`. Now they are
displayed as `KiB`.
add syntax highlighting to the readme
remove reference to Manifest from gemspec
